==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trimesitic
<hw>Tri`me*sit"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>mesit</ets>ylene + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a tribasic
acid, <chform>C6H3.(CO2)3</chform>, of the aromatic series, obtained, by
the oxidation of mesitylene, as a white crystalline substance.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>trimesic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trimester</ent>⟦br⟧
